<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF819FF886A1890041DC6F880" box="[372,442,1866,1888]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Scl. fui</emphasis>
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF819FF886AAD90041E6DF880" bold="true" box="[449,529,1866,1888]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">sp. nov.</emphasis>
paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104−106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108−110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104−106; 108, 110.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="47986554F826FFB76BAB97D91DFCFEFC" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0F3D36DFF826FFB76BAB97D91DFCFEFC" blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF826FFB76BAB97D91D3DFF50" bold="true" box="[199,321,151,176]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
With pale brownish dorsal colouration and faint indications of black tipped elytral apices, aedeagal sheath pattern and aedeagus very similar to that of 
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF826FFB769BB97F21F16FF35" box="[727,874,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Scl. 
<taxonomicName id="C8824D5CF826FFB7686497F21F16FF35" box="[776,874,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Sclerotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquatilis">aquatilis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
from which it is most obviously distinguished by the dorsal colouration. The molecular phylogeny (
<figureCitation id="97B92A5AF826FFB7698D97911F5BFF18" box="[737,807,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,870,892]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,198,845]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,193,849]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neighbour Joining bootstrap consensus tree of several aquatic fireflies in South East Asia, with firefly Pyrocoelia pectoralis as outgroup." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257998/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) suggested 
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF826FFB768D99791183DFF18" box="[949,1089,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicName id="C8824D5CF826FFB768D997911865FF18" box="[949,1049,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Sclerotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Sclerotia</taxonomicName>
fui
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF826FFB76F21979118D8FF18" bold="true" box="[1101,1188,223,248]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">sp. nov</emphasis>
. is distinct from 
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF826FFB76E1F97911C85FEFD" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Scl. 
<taxonomicName id="C8824D5CF826FFB76BFB964A1C85FEFD" box="[151,249,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Sclerotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquatilis" status="comb. nov.">aquatilis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="26C557B6F826FFB76A6C964A1DFCFEFC" box="[256,384,260,285]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF826FFB76A6C964A1D05FEFD" bold="true" box="[256,377,260,285]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">comb. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="47986554F826FFB76BAB9669184CFB9C" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" type="description">
<paragraph id="0F3D36DFF826FFB76BAB966918C5FD80" blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF826FFB76BAB96691D78FEA0" bold="true" box="[199,260,295,320]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Male</emphasis>
. 
<quantity id="C87A9B3AF826FFB76A7896661DE2FEDF" box="[276,414,296,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="9.4" metricValueMin="8.1" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="8.75" valueMax="9.4" valueMin="8.1">8.1–9.4 mm</quantity>
long, width/length 0.4. Colour: pronotum orange yellow, irregular retraction of fat body material in certain areas makes these areas appear darker; MS and MN yellow; elytra very light brown with small dark brown area at apex in dry pinned specimens, semitransparent with dark hind wing visible in ethanol preserved specimens (
<figureCitation id="97B92A5AF826FFB76A4C96DA1D04FE4C" box="[288,376,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 93 − 96" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1930,1952]" captionTargetBox="[212,1327,243,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[212,1374,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 93 − 96. Scl. flavida male (93, 94) and female (95, 96) Mt Bawangling, preserved in 70 % ethanol (NHMHAU). 93, 95 dorsal; 94, 96 ventral. Scale line is 5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258011/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 93</figureCitation>
); lateral margin paler yellow, semitransparent; sutural margin appearing paler as fat body material is irregularly scattered along the length, and this margin may not be white all along its length. Head dark brown, reddish brown above antennae and narrowly very pale brown immediately above antennae; antennae dark brown with anterior face of scape paler brown; labrum yellow; apices of palpi dark brown; ventral surface of body, and all legs yellow except for: dark brown tibiae and tarsi 1, tarsi 2 and posterior face of tibiae 2, tarsi 3, and pale brown posterior face of tibiae 3; posterior 1/3 of 
<date id="7B3C101FF826FFB769D595061E9EFD80" box="[697,738,583,608]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">V 5</date>
dark brown; dorsal abdomen pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F3D36DFF826FFB76BAB95231DECFD2D" blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Pronotum: W/L 1.7–2.1; L/BL 0.14–0.18; W/GHW 1.3–1.6. Elytron: 0.8−0.9 as long as total body length. Head: SIW/GHW 0.19; apical labial palpomeres with&gt;3 teeth. Abdomen: LO in 
<date id="7B3C101FF826FFB76F3895DE180AFD47" box="[1108,1142,656,679]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">V7</date>
with wide and relatively shallow emargination.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F3D36DFF826FFB76BAB95991F55FC28" blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Aedeagal sheath sclerites (
<figureCitation id="97B92A5AF826FFB76A9995991EE4FD10" box="[501,664,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 103−107</figureCitation>
): Very similar to 
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF826FFB7683295991F8EFD10" box="[862,1010,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Scl. 
<taxonomicName id="C8824D5CF826FFB768FC95991F8EFD10" box="[912,1010,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Sclerotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquatilis">aquatilis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
; ventral sclerite roughly triangular in outline with rounded distal end (
<figureCitation id="97B92A5AF826FFB7696595B21E16FCF4" box="[521,618,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 107</figureCitation>
); margins not thickened; anterolateral corners acute; right sclerite (
<figureCitation id="97B92A5AF826FFB76E0395B21CBEFCD8" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 103</figureCitation>
) with transverse projection apically acute and reaching across most of the entire portion of T8; right sclerite (
<figureCitation id="97B92A5AF826FFB76BF3940A1C83FCBC" box="[159,255,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 103</figureCitation>
) with three projections to the right, the posterior one apically acute, the median slender apically rounded and inclining dorsolaterally, and the third, longest projection, inclining ventrolaterally with a rounded hollow apex and arising in an emargination between the other two; left sclerite (
<figureCitation id="97B92A5AF826FFB768C994C2183BFC45" box="[933,1095,908,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 104−106</figureCitation>
) with three arms, all apically rounded, with anterior arm expanded, rounded and hollow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F3D36DFF826FFB76BAB949A18FCFBF0" blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Aedeagal sheath (
<figureCitation id="97B92A5AF826FFB76AF9949A1E47FC0C" box="[405,571,980,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 101, 102</figureCitation>
): sternite with oblique bar, and slightly off centred small median posterior emargination (
<figureCitation id="97B92A5AF826FFB76A5594B91DE0FBF0" box="[313,412,1015,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 102</figureCitation>
); median anterior margin of sheath tergite emarginated (
<figureCitation id="97B92A5AF826FFB76F7D94B91808FBF0" box="[1041,1140,1015,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 101</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F3D36DFF826FFB76BAB935218D6FBB8" blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="97B92A5AF826FFB76A2A93521D94FBD4" box="[326,488,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 108−110</figureCitation>
): L/ 
<geoCoordinate id="6AB65018F826FFB7697A93521E21FBD4" box="[534,605,1052,1076]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" precision="5555" value="-2.1">W 2.1</geoCoordinate>
−2.3. LL of unequal length (left slightly shorter than right); apices of LL rounded with inner apical margins toothed. Length basal piece/total length aedeagus 0.4−0.5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F3D36DFF826FFB76BAB932A184CFB9C" blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" box="[199,1072,1124,1149]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF826FFB76BAB932A1D62FB9D" bold="true" box="[199,286,1124,1149]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Female</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation id="97B92A5AF826FFB76A58932A1DBDFB9C" box="[308,449,1124,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 97 − 100" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[341,1279,506,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[260,1327,485,1945]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 97 − 100. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype male (97, 98) and female (99, 100) fresh collection Honghu City (NHMHAU). 97, 99 dorsal; 98, 100 ventral. Scale line is 5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258012/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 99, 100</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="C87A9B3AF826FFB76ABD932A1E24FB9C" box="[465,600,1124,1148]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8" metricValueMax="9.4" metricValueMin="8.2" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="8.8" valueMax="9.4" valueMin="8.2">8.2–9.4 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="C87A9B3AF826FFB769F2932A1F59FB9C" box="[670,805,1124,1149]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.45" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="3.45" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.3">3.3–3.6 mm</quantity>
wide; width/length 0.4.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="47986554F826FFB76BAB93C91D2DFB25" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="0F3D36DFF826FFB76BAB93C91D2DFB25" blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF826FFB76BAB93C91D32FB40" bold="true" box="[199,334,1159,1184]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species named for Xin Hua Fu who first observed and studied this backswimmer firefly in mainland 
<collectingCountry id="7795764FF826FFB76A6A93E21D31FB25" box="[262,333,1196,1221]" name="China" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="47986554F826FFB76BAB93811DF5FA04" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0F3D36DFF826FFB76BAB93811DF5FA04" blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF826FFB76BAB93811D47FB08" bold="true" box="[199,315,1231,1256]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has been misidentified as 
<taxonomicName id="C8824D5CF826FFB7699793811FB5FB08" box="[763,969,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="substriata">
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF826FFB7699793811FB5FB08" box="[763,969,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Luciola substriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in several publications. 
<bibRefCitation id="6B134B2EF826FFB76FB2939F19E0FB08" box="[1246,1436,1231,1256]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" refString="Fu, X. H., Ohba, N., Vencl, F. V. &amp; Lei, C. L. (2005 a) Structure, behavior and the life cycle of an aquatic firefly, Luciola substriata (Coleoptera: Lampyridae), in China. The Canadian Entomologist, 137, 83 - 90." type="journal article">
Fu 
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF826FFB76E68939F1941FB08" box="[1284,1341,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">et al.</emphasis>
(2005a)
</bibRefCitation>
reported on the biology of an aquatic firefly from 
<collectingRegion id="CD46F83DF826FFB7698693BA1FE1FAED" box="[746,925,1268,1293]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Hubei Province</collectingRegion>
which they identified as 
<taxonomicName id="C8824D5CF826FFB76FA793BA1C8AFAD0" authority="Gorham" authorityName="Gorham" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="substriata">
<emphasis id="3DF6EACDF826FFB76FA793BA19E0FAED" box="[1227,1436,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Luciola substriata</emphasis>
Gorham
</taxonomicName>
, a first record of the species from mainland 
<collectingCountry id="7795764FF826FFB769B292591F59FAD0" box="[734,805,1303,1328]" name="China" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">China</collectingCountry>
. 
